This paper deals with statistical estimation of high dimensional models with structured superposition, which involves decomposing parameters into multiple components with different structures. This is a common problem in machine learning and statistics, and is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. Given the focus on statistical analysis and estimation, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.ST (Statistics), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
